    AdjustableLine
    Lines are like Polygons except they have no interior.
    AdjustablePolygon
    Arbitrary polygon that can be moved around within a Scene.
    AllPlants
    A searchable database of all the plants a user can add to the their plot.
    BloomTimeComparator
    Sort a list of plants by bloom time, assuming descending default.
    BluePrint
    Allow the user detail the background of their plot with labels, and specify characteristics for some areas of their plot.
    BluePrintCharacteristics
    For the BluePrint Window, allow the user to specify the characteristics in specific areas of their plot.
    Canopy
    Vertical layers of the rain forest.
    CanopyComparator
    Compare plants by Canopy level, by default descending.
    Colors
    This is one of the stupidest things I've ever done in Java.
    CommandLineArgs
    Specifies all the command line arguments that may be passed to this program when initialized by a user or their OS.
    Controller
    Contains the start and real main, setups different components of the application.
    DistanceComparator
    Sort PlotObjects by their distance to a reference position.
    Download
    Where the user can export their plot as a PNG/JPEG, save it as a .gardenproject file, load a saved project, or exit.
    ExistingPlants
    Where a user can specify what plants already exist in their garden.
    GardenView
    General View descriptions.
    GenericLine
    A generic line object like a fence or a path that is a flat line with multiple points.
    GenericPolygon
    All PlotPolygons need to specify the Polygon and Anchors that will appear on the Plot Design window.
    GenericSpecial
    All other miscellaneous plot objects descend from GenericSpecial.
    ImageFileType
    The mulptiple ways a user can save an image of their plot in the Download screen
    Main
    Main entry point for the GardenProject application to bypass JavaFX errors.
    Model
    Updates the stage: Contains logic and data.
    Moisture
    Contains different levels of moisture in soil Used in Questionnaire and Plant Info TODO: More research on enum this seems complicated, consult the following link https://observant.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/article_attachments/203343303/Mgmt_Line_diagram_2.png or also google
    MoistureComparator
    Sort plants by Moisture, by default descending.
    Plant
    For every plant, there is a corresponding Plant object that contains as much information that can be loaded by PlantLoader.

    Plant data was gathered from public domain sources using Python scripts, and the plant data is stored as .json files in main.udel.plants.data
    PlantDataSource
    Specifies where the data for a Plant originated from, and a friendly name of that database.
    PlantInfo
    To display all the information of a Plant to the user.
    PlantLoader
    Load all the plants from local file databases.
    PlantNameComparator
    Compare Plants by Latin or common names, sorting by common names from A to Z by default.
    PlantSelection
    To display all the information of a Plant to the user.
    PlotBench
    Place to sit.
    PlotBirdBath
    Bath for birds.
    PlotDesign
    Heart of the application: Where the user can drag plants, obstacles, shade, text boxes, and interact with their virtual, top-down plot.
    PlotFence
    Fence that outlines a user's plot.
    PlotFlamingo
    Critical object.
    PlotForest
    High density forest.
    PlotGnome
    Another Critical object.
    PlotObject
    An object that can appear in PlotDesign must implement this interface.
    PlotObjects
    All objects that can appear in the PlotDesign and BluePrint windows.
    PlotObjectsFactory
    Facilitates the manufacturing of PlotObjects JavaFX Nodes, as they can display in an accordion.
    PlotOther
    Any other object in a garden.
    PlotPath
    A fence that typically goes around a user's plot.
    PlotPatio
    Paved outdoor area adjoining a house.
    PlotPlant
    Plant that can appear on the plot in PlotDesign.

    Special object that stays in the root of the udel.GardenProject.plotObjects package.

    This PlotObject is unique in that it does not have an accompanying PlotObjects enum constant, as the how a plant appears in an accordion is handled by the Plant class, and how it is rendered in the plot is defined by this PlotPlant's render() method, as all other PlotObject have.
    PlotPlayground
    Playground.
    PlotPool
    Chlorine-and-water filled of water.
    PlotRoad
    Path way for vehicles.
    PlotRock
    Large stone.
    PlotShed
    Outdoor storage structure.
    PlotTextLabel
    A customizable text label that a user can put on their Plot.
    PreviousSaves
    Displays a short table of where a user has recently saved Sessions on their disk.
    Questionnaire
    Basic questions about a user's plots that informs what plants are selected.
    Seasons
    General season descriptions, and combinations thereof.
    SeasonView
    Preview the garden as it will appear in every season and 1, 2, and 3 years down the line.
    Session
    Holds all the critical user-state information so that a .gardenproject file can be easily loaded in and out without much delay.

    Isolated so that it can be saved and loaded easily.

    All attributes should be adequately javadoc'd for future reference.

    NOTE: All attributes should be initialized to a default value, either in their attribute or the Session constructor.
    SoilTypeComparator
    Sort plants by SoilType, by default pH descending.
    SoilTypes
    SoilTypes from EarthEasy.com

    Acidity Levels from: Wikipedia GreenHarvest.com.au EarthEasy.com RHS.org.uk Contains different Soil Types, used in Questionnaire and Plant Info.
    Sunlight
    Contains the different sunlight and shade levels.
    Tutorial
    Presently: Basic text description run down of all the features of the program and how to use them.
    View
    Creates the stage: Loads graphics, images, and defines what the user sees.
    Welcome
    Welcome screen that first appears when the user starts the program.
    Window
    A window that can be displayed to the user.
    Windows
    All the windows that can be displayed to the user.
    YDistanceComparator
    Compare PlotObjects by Y-position, sorting from farthest to closest by default.
    Year
    General year descriptions.
